28/10/2003
MORELIA, Mexico -- Turkish State Minister Ali Babacan met separately Monday (27 October) with US Treasury Secretary John Snow and IMF First Deputy Managing Director Anne Krueger on the sidelines of the G-20 meeting in Morelia, Mexico. 
No information on the focus of discussions was released. 
But Babacan announced Monday that Turkey's draft Letter of Intent to the IMF was ready and would be submitted soon. 
The IMF Executive Board meets in November about releasing further loan tranches to Turkey.
In other news Monday, EU Commissioner for Enlargement Guenter Verheugen told a German newspaper that Turkey was presenting a "mixed picture" in its efforts to meet the membership criteria. 
He said he was not sure whether the European Commission would be able to decide at the end of 2004 whether to start accession talks with Ankara. 
(Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2, AFP - 27/10/03)
